​Here is a concise summary of the Eiffel Tower based on the information available:​

Summary
Fact 1: The Eiffel Tower was designed by engineers Maurice Koechlin and Émile Nouguier and constructed by Gustave Eiffel's company for the 1889 Exposition Universelle in Paris.

Fact 2: Standing at 330 meters (1,083 feet), it was the tallest man-made structure in the world until the completion of the Chrysler Building in New York in 1930.

Fact 3: Originally met with criticism, the tower has become a global icon of France and is one of the most visited monuments in the world
